+# Mutter Butter Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Build a GNOME 50 Shell extension that manages windows on a configurable grid with live-scaling "postage stamp" behavior for inactive windows.
+
+**Architecture:** Seven ES modules (gridEngine, scaleManager, focusTracker, stampPlacer, dragHandler, inputRouter, settings) orchestrated by extension.js. Pure-logic modules (gridEngine, stampPlacer, focusTracker) are unit-tested with a standalone GJS test harness. GNOME Shell integration modules use Clutter.Clone for live previews and Shell.util_set_hidden_from_pick for input routing.
+
+**Tech Stack:** GJS (ES modules), GNOME Shell 50 APIs (Meta, Clutter, St, Shell), GSettings with relocatable schemas, libadwaita (Adw.PreferencesWindow)
+
+**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-03-mutter-butter-design.md`
+
+---
+
+## File Structure
+
+```
+mutter-butter/
+├── metadata.json                    # Extension metadata (uuid, shell-version, etc.)
+├── extension.js                     # enable()/disable() orchestration, signal wiring
+├── prefs.js                         # Preferences UI (runs in separate GTK process)
+├── stylesheet.css                   # Grid overlay and stamp layer styling
+├── schemas/
+│   └── org.gnome.shell.extensions.mutter-butter.gschema.xml
+├── lib/
+│   ├── constants.js                 # Scale steps, window type filters, timing constants
+│   ├── gridEngine.js                # Per-monitor grid math, cell allocation, best-fit
+│   ├── stampPlacer.js               # In-place, shelf, pack placement strategies
+│   ├── focusTracker.js              # Focus rank list, auto-shrink/restore triggers
+│   ├── scaleManager.js              # Clone lifecycle, allocation-based scaling, state
+│   ├── inputRouter.js               # Clone containers, pick hiding, click handlers
+│   ├── dragHandler.js               # Full-size grab-op drag + stamp manual drag
+│   └── windowStateHandler.js        # Fullscreen, maximized, tiled, minimized handling
+└── tests/
+    ├── run.js                       # GJS standalone test runner
+    ├── gridEngine.test.js           # Grid math tests
+    ├── stampPlacer.test.js          # Placement strategy tests
+    └── focusTracker.test.js         # Rank list and cascade tests
+```
+
